Parameter.name: DATA_CODING_SCHEME
Parameter.Description: Data coding scheme in hexadecimal - 8 bits - 00 to FF

Parameter.name: PS_MCS_12
Parameter.Description: Puncturing modulation coding schemes 1 and 2: could be set for all DL MCS

Parameter.name: PS_MCS_123
Parameter.Description: Puncturing modulation coding schemes 1,2 and 3: could be set for DL MCS 3,4,7,8,9

Parameter.name: MULTISLOT_CONFIG
Parameter.Description: Multislot configuration - If MAX is selected, value will be retrieved from DeviceCatalog.xml

Parameter.name: MMS_SUBJECT
Parameter.Description: Subject of the MMS in text format

Parameter.name: SMS_TYPE
Parameter.Description: SMS Type for IMS, either TGPP (3GPP) or TGP2 (3GPP2)

Parameter.name: SMS_TEXT
Parameter.Description: Text content of the MMS / SMS.

Parameter.name: ATTACHMENT_FILE
Parameter.Description: Name of a file, present in the multimedia path of the device or local computer, that will be attached.

Parameter.name: MMS_TYPE
Parameter.Description: Describes the type of MMS that will be built. Should be "picture" or "text". "picture" for a MMS with subject, text and an attached picture. "text" for a MMS with subject and text only.

Parameter.name: NETWORK_TYPE
Parameter.Description: The string value corresponding to the current Network Type on which the DUT is camped | UNKNOWN | GPRS | EGPRS | UMTS | CDMA | EVDO_0 | EVDO_A | 1xRTT | HSDPA | HSUPA | HSPA | IDEN | EVDO_B | LTE | EHRPD | HSPAP | 3xRTT | EVDV | UMB

Parameter.name: NETWORK_PREFERENCES
Parameter.Description: The string value corresponding to the preferred Network Type on which the DUT should be | 3G_PREF = WCDMA_preferred 2G_ONLY = GSM_only 3G_ONLY = WCDMA_only 2G_3G = GSM_auto_PRL CDMA_PREF = CDMA_auto_PRL CDMA_ONLY = CDMA_only EVDO_ONLY = EvDo_only GLOBAL = GSM_CDMA_auto_PRL 4G_PREF_US = LTE_CDMA_auto_PRL 4G_PREF = LTE_GSM_auto_PRL WORLD_MODE = LTE_GSM_CDMA_auto_PRL 4G_ONLY = LTE_only.

Parameter.name: VC_TYPE
Parameter.Description: Voice Call Type - MO [Mobile Originated]|MT [Mobile Terminated]

Parameter.name: RELEASE_VC_TYPE
Parameter.Description: Release Voice Call Type - MR [Mobile Released]|NR [Network Released]

Parameter.name: IS_EMERGENCY_NUMBER
Parameter.Description: This parameter indicates whether the phone number is an emergency number or not

Parameter.name: RADIO_ACCESS_BEARER
Parameter.Description: Radio Access Bearer - 64k | 128k | 384k | MAX - If MAX is selected, value will be retrieved from DeviceCatalog.xml

Parameter.name: CPC_TTI
Parameter.Description: CPC [Continuous Packet Connectivity] feature uses 2 Transmission Time Interval : 2 [TTI =2ms] and 10 [TTI =10ms]

Parameter.name: CQI_REPORTING_SCHEME
Parameter.Description: Channel Quality Indicator reporting scheme - Fixed value or UE reported - FIXED|REPORTED

Parameter.name: MAC_D_PDU_SIZE
Parameter.Description: PS Data HS-DSCH MAC-d PDU Size - BITS336|BITS656

Parameter.name: CPC_DEACT_TYPE
Parameter.Description: CPC Deactivation type during data transfer - CPC_OFF | HS_SCCH_ORDER | PDP_DEACT

Parameter.name: ANTENNA
Parameter.Description: Number of antennas - could be 1 or 2

Parameter.name: LTE_SIGNAL_MODE
Parameter.Description: Operation mode to set : BSE or SA

Parameter.name: LTE_PHYSICAL_CELL_ID
Parameter.Description: Physical Cell Id used to scramble and differentiate data from different transmitters - 0 to 503

Parameter.name: CELL_ID
Parameter.Description: Cell Setup : "A" for A-cell or "B" for B-cell

Parameter.name: TYPE0_BITMAP
Parameter.Description: DL Resource alloc Type#0 Bitmap in decimal (hex: 0x0000001 to 0x1FFFFFF)

Parameter.name: UL_GRANT_MODE
Parameter.Description: UL GRANT MODE to set: AUTO or FIXEDMAC

Parameter.name: ST_EQUIPMENT_CONFIG_FILE
Parameter.Description: System Test Equipment Configuration file - ST\telephony\Configurations\filename (without xml extension)

Parameter.name: MMGR_CONFIG_FILE
Parameter.Description: Absolute path of the mmgr's configuration file - /system/etc/telephony/mmgr.conf

Parameter.name: SCENARIO_PATH
Parameter.Description: Path to the scenario filename to load on PXT

Parameter.name: AT_PROXY_LAUNCH_MODE
Parameter.Description: AT proxy launch mode. Possible values: NORMAL | TUNNELING

Parameter.name: AT_COMMAND_RETURN_CODE
Parameter.Description: AT command return code. Possible values: OK | ERROR

Parameter.name: MOVE_OUT_OF_COVERAGE_SELECTOR
Parameter.Description: Indicates when DUT should move out of coverage, when send or receive MMS. Possible values are: 0 (don't perform loss of coverage), 1 (before sending MMS), 2 (while receiving MMS).

Parameter.name: IMS_PARAMETER_FILE
Parameter.Description: The path to the IMS parameter file to use to create the IMS_Config.ini file on the device.

Parameter.name: MMS_TEXT_REPEAT
Parameter.Description: Indicates the number of times we want to repeat a text in an MMS body.

Parameter.name: IMS_REGISTRATION_OPERATION
Parameter.Description: Indicates the action to perform for IMS registration. REGISTER (perform IMS registration normally) or CHECK_ONLY (only check that the IMS status is REGISTERED).
